questionTemplates.text:
W: What color do you like to wear?
M: I like to wear black, blue, and white. How about you?
{a}

M: Would you like a cup of tea?
W: I'd rather have a cool drink, please.
{a}

F: When shall I return the book?
M: Seven days later.
{a}

W: How far is it to the courthouse?
M: Well, you go down this street for two more blocks, then turn left onto Main and go four blocks, then turn right onto Washington Avenue for two blocks, oh, no, not two blocks but one block: it's right there on the coiner, you can't miss it.
{a}

M: Miss Smith, I told Dr. Brown that I would call him in the Houston office at ten o'clock by their time. Please find out the time difference for me so that I'll know when to place the call.
W: It's two hours earlier in Houston, sir. I know without looking it up because my sister lives there.
{a}

M: Do you think it is a good idea to double the price of cigarettes?
W: Yes, because people won't want to smoke as much any more.
{a}

M: Miss, what time is Flight NH906 for New York due to depart?
W: It leaves at 3:45. but you must check in one hour ahead of departure.
{a}

F: Would you like something to drink? What about a glass of milk?
M: No, thanks, I think I'd like something to eat.
{a}

W: Which one do you like,spring or autumn,Mr Wang?
M: Oh, summer is my favourite season. I like swimming very much.
{a}

M: Your clean shirts are hanging in the closet.
W: Great! So you did get the laundry done after all!
{a}

M: Did the professor give an assignment for Monday?
W: Nothing to read, but we have to see a movie and write a short comment about it.
{a}

W: I'm not sure whether I have enough money for all these things. I've only got 100 dollars.
M: You've got enough money for everything, and you can still get five dollars fifty back.
{a}

F: Excuse me, how can I get to Star Restaurant?
M: Go along the road and turn to the right at the third crossing.
{a}

M: How does Nancy like the new dress she bought in Rome?
W: She said she would never have bought an Italian style dress if she had known Mary had already got such a dress.
{a}

M: The front tyre is flat, and the seat needs to be raised.
W: Well. Why not take it to Mr. Brown?
{a}

F: Look at these glasses. This one's even got lipstick on it.
M: I'm sorry, madam. I'll bring you another clean one right away.
{a}

W: Are you clear about the instructions?
M: Well, would you mind repeating them?
{a}

M: These oranges are nice. How much are they?
W: They are sixty cents a pound.
{a}

M: I thought the girl was good.
F: Did you?
{a}

M: I must say, Miss, the food was great and I've never had better service.
W: Well, thank you, sir. I'll pass your praise on to the cook and the manager. And thanks too for the tip.
{a}

W: Er... what would you like to drink, tea, coffee or orange juice?
M: Er... maybe.., some coffee, please.
{a}

W: I wonder where I can take my girlfriend for dinner after work tonight.
M: Have you been to the Chinese Restaurant near the school?
{a}

M: I paid 45 dollars for this pair of pants.
W: Look at mine. They were twelve dollars cheaper than yours.
{a}

W: Has the latest magazine arrived yet? Today's already Wednesday.
M: Sorry, it's late. Probably not until the day after tomorrow.
{a}
